1. The turning points satisfy $E=V(a)=F\,a\implies a=E/F$.  
2. The period is  
$$T=4\int_{0}^{a}\frac{dx}{v(x)} 
=4\int_{0}^{a}\frac{m\,dx}{\sqrt{2m\bigl(E-Fx\bigr)}}
=4\sqrt{\frac{m}{2}}\int_{0}^{E/F}\frac{dx}{\sqrt{E-Fx}}\,. $$  
3. Use $u=E-Fx$, $dx=-du/F$, so  
$$\int_{0}^{E/F}\frac{dx}{\sqrt{E-Fx}}
=\frac{1}{F}\int_{E}^{0}\frac{-du}{\sqrt{u}}
=\frac{1}{F}\int_{0}^{E}u^{-1/2}du
=\frac{2\sqrt{E}}{F}\,. $$  
4. Thus  
$$T=4\sqrt{\frac{m}{2}}\;\frac{2\sqrt{E}}{F}
=\frac{4\sqrt{2\,m\,E}}{F}\,. $$  
5. The oscillation frequency is  
$$\nu=\frac1T=\frac{F}{4\sqrt{2\,m\,E}}\,. $$
